value.title: Biden approval rating: Thumbs up overall, but thumbs down on immigration: poll
value.excerpt: A new national poll indicates that most Americans approve of the overall job President Biden is doing in the White House. But, according to AP-NORC survey released Monday, the president’s numbers are mixed on gun violence and underwater on immigration.

value.title: Trump leaves Florida for summer in New Jersey after Mother’s Day brunch: report
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump spent Mother’s Day having brunch with wife Melania and son Barron, before jetting out to spend the summer in New Jersey, according to a report.

value.title: Pelosi, Biden praise moms on Mother's Day amid progressive talk of 'birthing people'
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and the White House issued Mother's Day messages on Sunday as some progressives use the term "birthing people" instead.

value.title: Biden admin faces lack of icebreakers, increasing Russian and Chinese threats in Arctic
value.excerpt: One of the least talked-about challenges for the new administration is one that's been brewing for years, long before Donald Trump's presidency: growing challenges to the United States' ability to assert its will in the Arctic.

value.title: Pence trips spark further 2024 White House race speculation
value.excerpt: In a move that will spark further 2024 speculation, former Vice President Mike Pence will headline a major Republican Party dinner and fundraising event in early June in New Hampshire, the state that for a century has held the first primary in the race for the White House.

value.title: Biden administration has spent $3B on migrant facility contracts: report
value.excerpt: The Biden administration has reportedly spent $3 billion in contracts to house unaccompanied children at the border – as it continues to deal with a continued influx of migrants coming to the border each day.

value.excerpt: The Biden White House released its first round of visitor logs Friday in an effort to "restore integrity, transparency, and trust in government," the administration said.

value.excerpt: "Real Time" host Bill Maher wondered if Republican Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis will run for president in 2024 -- regardless of whether he receives former President Trump's "blessing."

value.title: Biden Labor Secretary: Closed schools 'keeping people from getting back in the workforce'
value.excerpt: Labor Secretary Marty Walsh drew a parallel Friday between the continued fight over reopening schools for in-person instruction and the  April jobs report, which fell far short of experts' predictions.

value.title: Stefanik says GOP needs to be 'one team' in 2022, is committed to working with Trump
value.excerpt: Rep. Elise Stefanik said Thursday that Republicans need to work as "one team" in 2022 to win back the House of Representatives, comments made as she emerges as the favorite to replace Rep. Liz Cheney as the House Republican Conference chair.

value.title: Liz Cheney, facing GOP leadership removal, takes swipe at Trump 'cult'
value.excerpt: Rep. Liz Cheney (R-WY) wrote that the Republican Party is at a "turning point" and must decide “whether we will join Trump’s crusade to delegitimize and undo the legal outcome of the 2020 election, with all the consequences that might have.”

value.title: Democrats Schiff, Omar celebrate Facebook's indefinite Trump ban
value.excerpt: Democrats, including Rep. Adam Schiff, D-Calif., and Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., praised Facebook's indefinite ban of former President Trump.

value.title: Donald Trump promises supporters will be ‘very happy’ when he makes 2024 announcement
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Tuesday promised his supporters would be very happy when he eventually makes his announcement about whether he will run in the 2024 presidential election.

value.title: DOJ ordered to turn over Trump obstruction of justice memo
value.excerpt: A judge has ordered the Department of Justice (DOJ) to turn over an internal memo from March 2019 that then-Attorney General Bill Barr cited as his reason not to charge former President Trump with obstruction of justice following the Mueller investigation.

value.excerpt: President Biden traveled to Philadelphia's 30th Street Station Friday to celebrate the 50th anniversary of Amtrak’s first rail ride, from New York City to Philadelphia, and tout a grand future for the federally funded train system.
